import{_ as o,o as t,c as r,a,d as e,e as s,b as i}from"./app-a6eacc5a.js";const p={},n=e("h1",{id:"why-do-some-people-live-to-100",tabindex:"-1"},[e("a",{class:"header-anchor",href:"#why-do-some-people-live-to-100","aria-hidden":"true"},"#"),s(" Why Do Some People Live to 100 ？")],-1),d=i('<p>Why do some people live to be 100 ?</p><p>Because they&#39;re taking these.</p><p>Just kidding. There&#39;s no pill to make you live longer.</p><p>But scientists are trying to figure out why some people live healthy lives beyond a hundred, when the average <em>life-span</em> in the U.S. is only 78.</p><p>The good <code>old-fashioned</code> advice is: eat a low-fat, high-fiber diet with lots of fruits and <code>veggies</code>, get plenty of exercise, and manage stress by staying positive and <em>keeping up</em> relationships with friends and family.</p><p>But here&#39;s where the research gets <code>tricky</code>.</p><p>Plenty of people who live beyond 100 don&#39;t follow these rules.</p><p>Some of them smoke, are generally <code>cranky</code>, and don&#39;t eat quite as well as they should.</p><p>So, what do they have <em>working in their favor</em>?</p><p>The right <code>genes</code>.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 为什么有些人能活到100岁?<br> 因为他们拿走了这些。<br> 只是开玩笑。没有什么药能让你活得更久。<br> 但科学家们正试图弄清楚为什么有些人能健康地活到100岁以上，而美国人的平均寿命只有78岁。<br> 传统的好建议是:吃低脂肪、高纤维的饮食，多吃水果和蔬菜，多锻炼，通过保持积极的心态和与朋友和家人保持良好的关系来管理压力。<br> 但这就是研究的棘手之处。<br> 很多活到100岁以上的人都没有遵守这些规则。<br> 他们中的一些人抽烟，脾气暴躁，吃得也不太好。<br> 那么，他们有什么有利条件呢?<br> 正确的基因。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> life-span -&gt; 寿命<br> keep up -&gt; 保持<br> working in their favor -&gt; 对他们有利</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> old-fashioned<br><code>英 [ˌəʊld ˈfæʃ(ə)nd]美 [ˌoʊld ˈfæʃ(ə)nd]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 过时的，老式的；（观点、习俗、价值观等）守旧的，传统的；（表情）反对的</p></blockquote><p>veggies<br><code>英 [ˈvedʒɪz]美 [ˈvedʒiz]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 蔬菜；素菜类；素食主义者（veggy 的复数形式）</p></blockquote><p>tricky ( trickier, trickiest )<br><code>英 [ˈtrɪki]美 [ˈtrɪki]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 难对付的，棘手的；狡猾的，诡计多端的</p></blockquote><p>cranky<br><code>英 [ˈkræŋki]美 [ˈkræŋki]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 暴躁的；古怪的；动摇的</p></blockquote><p>genes<br><code>英 [dʒiːnz]美 [dʒiːnz]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 基因（gene 的复数）</p></blockquote></details><p>No, not that kind of &#39;jeans&#39;.</p><p>This kind.</p><p>The strongest predictor that someone will live a long time is whether that person has lots of long-lived relatives.</p><p>Scientists think these people might actually be <code>aging</code> more slowly on a <code>cellular</code> level.</p><p>As we live, our cells and DNA are getting damaged by free <code>radicals</code> and other forces.</p><p>Our bodies repair most of the damage, but as we age many of us can&#39;t quite keep up.</p><p>So, those who get a birthday <em>shout-out</em> from Willard Scott might actually be more efficient at this kind of repair.</p><p>Researchers are looking for these specific genetic <code>traits</code> in hopes of turning them into an anti-aging <code>therapy</code>.</p><p>But, what can <em>the rest of</em> us do in the <code>meantime</code>?</p><p>Eat your fruits and veggies.</p><details class="custom-container details"><summary>translation</summary><p><strong>sentence:</strong><br> 不，不是那种“牛仔裤”。<br> 这类。<br> 预测一个人长寿的最有力因素是这个人是否有很多长寿的亲戚。<br> 科学家们认为，这些人实际上可能在细胞水平上衰老得更慢。<br> 当我们活着的时候，我们的细胞和DNA会受到自由基和其他力量的破坏。<br> 我们的身体会修复大部分损伤，但随着年龄的增长，很多人无法跟上。<br> 所以，那些得到威拉德·斯科特生日祝福的人实际上可能在这种修复方面更有效率。<br> 研究人员正在寻找这些特定的基因特征，希望将它们转化为一种抗衰老疗法。<br> 但是，在此期间，我们其他人能做些什么呢?<br> 多吃水果和蔬菜。</p><p><strong>phrase:</strong><br> shout-out -&gt; 公开道谢；当众问候<br> the rest of -&gt; 剩余的部分：指某个整体中剩余的部分。</p><p><strong>word:</strong><br> aging<br><code>英 [ˈeɪdʒɪŋ]美 [ˈeɪdʒɪŋ]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 变老的，变旧的<br> n. 老化，变老<br> v. 变老，老化；（使）显老；（使）变陈（age 的现在分词形式）</p></blockquote><p>cellular<br><code>英 [ˈseljələ(r)]美 [ˈseljələr]</code></p><blockquote><p>adj. 由细胞组成的，细胞的；（电话系统）蜂窝状的，蜂窝式的；（毛毯、背心等织物）织成网眼的；由小单位元（部分）组成的，分格式的<br> n. 移动电话</p></blockquote><p>radicals<br><code>美 [ˈrædɪkl]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 自由基；激进分子；[数]根基（radical 的复数）</p></blockquote><p>traits<br><code>英 [treɪts]美 [treɪts]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 特性，特质，性格（trait 的复数）</p></blockquote><p>therapy [ 复数 therapies ]<br><code>英 [ˈθerəpi]美 [ˈθerəpi]</code></p><blockquote><p>n. 治疗，疗法；心理治疗；（对身心健康）有裨益的活动</p></blockquote><p>meantime<br><code>英 [ˈmiːntaɪm]美 [ˈmiːntaɪm]</code></p><blockquote><p>adv. 同时，在此期间<br> n. 其时，其间</p></blockquote></details>',22);function c(l,h){return t(),r("div",null,[n,a(" 为什么有些人能活到100岁? "),d])}const u=o(p,[["render",c],["__file","30-live-to-100.html.vue"]]);export{u as default};
